<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7307039>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A–E. Specimen found in the vial of Carteronius helluo Simon, 1896 (MNHN 10.611), which actually corresponds to the holotype of Carteronius scriptus Simon, 1896: A male holotype habitus, lateral view; B left palp, prolateral view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E original label. F–J. Specimen found in the vial of Carteronius scriptus (MNHN 14.625), which actually corresponds to the holotype of Carteronius helluo: F male holotype habitus, lateral view; G same, frontal view; H right palp, ventral view; I same, retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view; J original label." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7307039/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7307047>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Carteronius sudanus (Karsch, 1880) comb. nov.: A male palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view; C epigynum, ventral view; D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; C, conductor; MA, median apophysis; VL, ventral lobe; ML, medial lobe; DL, dorsal lobe; AS, spur; CDv, ventral sector of the copulatory duct; CDd, dorsal sector of the copulatory duct; ST2, secondary spermatheca; ST1 primary spermatheca. Scale: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7307047/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7307059>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Carteronius arboreus sp. nov.: A male palp, ventral view (arrow: embolar process); B same, retrolateral view; C epigynum, ventral view (arrow: transversal ridge); D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; C, conductor; MA, median apophysis; VL, ventral lobe; ML, medial lobe; DL, dorsal lobe; AS, spur; CDv, ventral sector of the copulatory duct; CDd, dorsal sector of the copulatory duct; ST2, secondary spermatheca; ST1 primary spermatheca. Scale: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7307059/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7307065>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Carteronius ashanti sp. nov.: A male palp, ventral view (arrow: retrolateral apical tegular process); B same, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; C, conductor; MA, median apophysis; VL, ventral lobe; ML, medial lobe; DL, dorsal lobe; AS, spur. Scale: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7307065/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7307051>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Carteronius sudanus (Karsch, 1880) comb. nov.: A epigynum, ventral view; B same, posterior view; C same, dorsal view; D same, latero-dorsal view (arrow: glands duct). Abbreviations: CO, copulatory opening; CDv, ventral sector of the copulatory duct; CDd, dorsal sector of the copulatory duct; LP, lateral plates of the posterior sector; ST2, secondary spermatheca; ST1 primary spermatheca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7307051/files/figure.png" ;
